{
  "text": "These relatively short-term studies have encouraged widespread promulgation and acceptance of the simple model for the bottom-up influence of precipitation on rodents and other consumers in arid ecosystems. This model has been widely applied not only to account for the dynamics of desert rodent populations but also to explain how outbreaks of hantavirus and peaks of predator populations can be related to the trophic chain extending from precipitation through plants and mammalian herbivores to higher trophic levels [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
